		<td><b>Re: Making top-loader NES as good as AV Famicom?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't <em>know</em> the &quot;right&quot; way to do it, but I would start with:<br />Re-implement the frontloader's video pathway, using dedicated wires (from the regulator) for power supply rails, bypass capacitors, and coaxial cable. If there's still PPU noise coupled in, maybe give the PPU a dedicated power rail and/or regulator.<br /><br />The reverse-engineered Electronix corp schematic seems to indicate it's just a pair of PNP and NPN common-emitter current buffers, but.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


